$ SQL*Plus: VARIABLE
@ variable

`variable` declares a bind → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/_variables[variable] which then can be used in → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement[SQL Statements] or
(anonymous) → development/databases/Oracle/PL-SQL/block[PL/SQL blocks].

The current value of the bind variable can be shown with `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/print`.

code {
variable num number
exec :num := 42
print num
code }

code {
var  last_create_time varchar2(19)
begin
   select
      to_char(max(created), 'yyyy-mm-dd hh24:mi:ss') into :last_create_time
   from
      user_objects;
end;
/

begin
   dbms_output.put_line('Last creation time: ' || :last_create_time);
end;
/
code }

{ Datatypes

  A bind variable can be set to one of the following data types:
    • `number `
    • `char [(n [char | byte])]`
    • `varchar2 [(n [char | byte])]`
    • `nchar`
    • `nchar(n)`
    • `nvarchar2(n)`
    • `clob`
    • `nclob`
    • `blob`
    • `bfile`
    • `refcursor`
    • `binary_float`
    • `binary_double`

  There is no *date* datatype!

}

sa:

  Using → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/_variables[variables] in SQL*Plus.

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus
